---
source: crates/ridge-lexer/tests/snapshots.rs
expression: render(RATE_LIMITER)
---
0..467 DOC_COMMENT "Token-bucket rate limiter implemented as an actor.  The Limiter actor holds\ncapacity, a floating-point token count, a refill rate (tokens per second), and\nthe timestamp of the last refill.  On each `allow` request it refills tokens\nproportional to elapsed time, then grants or denies the request.\nFive worker actors each send 20 requests at random sub-second delays; after all\nworkers finish they send their tallies to a Collector actor, which prints totals."
